Package pkgController

Class EditGardenController

java.lang.Object
pkgController.EditGardenController
public class EditGardenController
extends java.lang.Object
Author:
Ryan Dean Controller for Edit Garden screen. Holds handlers and facilitates communication between EditGardenView and EditGardenModel.

  • Constructor Details

    • EditGardenController

      public EditGardenController​(View view, EditGardenView gardenView, java.lang.String loadName)
      Constructor loads a serialized gardenModel and disperses that data to model and view if loadName present. If not, reads serialized information from Select Plants and Draw Garden screens, and disperses that data to model and view instead.
      Parameters:
      view - EditGardenView that is the view class for this screen. Information necessary for display is sent there.
      gardenView - EditGardenModel, the model class for this screen. All garden and plant information is sent there.
      loadName - String representing user-input name for the garden to load. Null if not loading a garden.

    • clickedSave

      public void clickedSave​(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)

      event - The ActionEvent caused by clicking the save button.

    • clickedPrint

      public void clickedPrint​(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
      Handler for clicking print button. Saves a snapshot of the garden stackpane in EditGardenView.
      Parameters:
      event - The ActionEvent caused by clicking the print button.

    • fetchGardenInfo

      public void fetchGardenInfo()
      Helper method used when loading a saved garden. Updates view according to all data stored in the loaded gardenModel.

    • drag

      public void drag​(javafx.scene.input.MouseEvent event)
      Handler for dragging a PlantView node. Updates position in model, then updates view accordingly. Runs checks for outside bounds/overlapping spreads.
      Parameters:
      event - The MouseEvent caused by dragging a PlantView node.

    • press

      public void press​(javafx.scene.input.MouseEvent event)
      Handler for clicking a PlantView node in the view's DragDropCarousel. Prompts model and view to transport plant from carousel to garden.
      Parameters:
      event - MouseEvent caused by clicking on a PlantView node.

    • release

      public void release​(javafx.scene.input.MouseEvent event)
      Handler for releasing mouse button after dragging a PlantView node. Prompts model to update budget/lep info and send that to view.
      Parameters:
      event - MouseEvent caused by releasing mouse button on PlantView node.
